<inglise> 1999/207/EC: Council Decision of 9 March 1999 on the reform of the Standing Committee on Employment and repealing Decision 70/532/EEC </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU OTSUS 1999/207/E&Uuml; alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee &uuml;mberkorraldamise ja otsuse 70/532/EM&Uuml; kehtetuks tunnistamise kohta 9. m&auml;rts 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 145 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 145, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas, in its Resolutions of 15 December 1997 on the 1998 Employment Guidelines (1), and of 22 February 1999 on the 1999 Employment Guidelines (2), the Council affirmed that the social partners at the levels would be involved in all stages of the coordinated employment strategy and would make an important contribution to the implementation of the Guidelines and that that contribution would be regularly assessed; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) n&otilde;ukogu on oma 15. detsembri 1997. aasta resolutsioonis (1998. aasta t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivesuuniste kohta (1)) ja 22. veebruari 1999. aasta resolutsioonis (1999. aasta t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivesuuniste kohta (2)) kinnitanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled k&otilde;ikidel tasanditel peaksid osalema koosk&otilde;lastatud t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivestrateegia igas etapis ja andma oma olulise panuse suuniste rakendamisse, ning s&auml;testanud, et seda panust tuleks regulaarselt hinnata; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the social partners' contribution to the coordinated employment strategy should be taken into account both at the level of the Employment Guidelines themselves and in examining their consistency with the Broad Economic Policy Guidelines, in order to provide for greater synergy and with a view to incorporating the objective of a high level of employment into the drawing-up and implementation of the Community's policies; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte panust koosk&otilde;lastatud t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivestrateegiasse tuleks arvesse v&otilde;tta nii t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivesuuniste tasandil kui ka anal&uuml;&uuml;sides nende j&auml;rjepidevust majanduspoliitiliste &uuml;ldsuuniste seisukohalt, et paraneks koostoime ning t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive k&otilde;rge tase kui eesm&auml;rk kajastuks &uuml;henduse poliitika kujundamisel ja elluviimisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas, in its Resolution of 18 July 1997 on the Commission communication concerning the development of the social dialogue at Community level (3), the European Parliament calls for the Standing Committee on Employment to be reformed as a matter of urgency and for coordination mechanisms to be introduced between that Committee and the Employment and Labour Market Committee; whereas, in its Resolution of 18 November 1998, the European Parliament welcomed the initiatives taken with a view to the reform of the Standing Committee on Employment; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Euroopa Parlament on oma 18. juuli 1997. aasta resolutsioonis (komisjoni teatise kohta sotsiaalk&uuml;simustealase dialoogi arendamisest &uuml;henduse tasandil (3)) n&otilde;udnud alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee kiiret &uuml;mberkorraldamist ning koosk&otilde;lastusmehhanismide loomist k&otilde;nealuse komitee ja t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ning t&ouml;&ouml;turukomitee vahel; 18. novembri 1998. aasta resolutsiooniga tervitas Euroopa Parlament alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee &uuml;mberkorraldamiseks tehtud algatusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the Economic and Social Committee in its opinion of 29 January 1997 (4) on the same Commission communication stated that the Standing Committee on Employment was to be given a higher profile; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee on 29. jaanuaril 1997 selle sama komisjoni teatise kohta esitatud arvamuses (4) kinnitanud, et alalisele t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomiteele tuleb omistada suuremat t&auml;htsust; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas, in its communication of 20 May 1998 on adapting and promoting the social dialogue at Community level, the Commission considered that the new context of Community social dialogue and the incorporation of a new employment title in the Amsterdam Treaty justified reforming the Standing Committee on Employment; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) komisjon on oma 20. mai 1998. aasta teatises (sotsiaalk&uuml;simustealase dialoogi kohandamise ja edendamise kohta &uuml;henduse tasandil) leidnud, et &uuml;henduse tasandil toimuva sotsiaalk&uuml;simustealase dialoogi tingimused on muutunud ning uue t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivet k&auml;sitleva jaotise l&uuml;litamine Amsterdami lepingusse &otilde;igustavad alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee &uuml;mberkorraldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas it seems advisable to maintain the structure of the Standing Committee on Employment while making the adjustments necessary to improve its operation; whereas it seems desirable to incorporate this reform into a new decision replacing Council Decision 70/532/EEC of 14 December 1970 setting up the Standing Committee on Employment (5) in the European Communities; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) n&auml;ib otstarbekas s&auml;ilitada alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee struktuur, tehes samal ajal vajalikke kohandusi selle tegevuse t&otilde;hustamiseks; on soovitav l&uuml;litada see reform uude otsusesse, mis asendab n&otilde;ukogu 14. detsembri 1970. aasta otsust 70/532/EM&Uuml; Euroopa &uuml;henduste alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee loomise kohta (5); </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas it is desirable that the social partners' delegations should cover the whole economy but that, in order to allow the efficient and orderly conduct of business in the Committee, the number of their representatives should be reduced; whereas the respective social partners' representation should be adequately coordinated; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) on soovitav, et t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte delegatsioonid h&otilde;lmaksid k&otilde;iki majandusvaldkondi, kuid samal ajal tuleks komitee t&otilde;husa ja n&otilde;uetekohase tegevuse huvides esindajate arvu nendes v&auml;hendada; eri t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte esindatus peaks olema piisaval m&auml;&auml;ral koosk&otilde;lastatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas the social partners at national level also play an important role in the implementation, in the Member States, of the coordinated employment strategy; whereas they may be involved in an appropriate manner in the fulfilment of the Committee's functions; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) siseriiklikul tasandil on t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooltel oluline roll koosk&otilde;lastatud t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivestrateegia elluviimisel liikmesriikides; nad v&otilde;ivad asjakohasel viisil osaleda komitee &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the Committee may deem it appropriate to meet in restricted formation in accordance with this Decision and with rules set out in its Rules of Procedure; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) komitee v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva otsuse ning oma t&ouml;&ouml;korras s&auml;testatud eeskirjade p&otilde;hjal pidada asjakohaseks koguneda piiratud koosseisus; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas Article 1(3) of Council Decision 97/16/EC of 20 December 1996 setting up an Employment and Labour Market Committee (6) provides that that Committee will maintain an appropriate liaison with the Standing Committee on Employment, </inglise>
<eesti> 10) n&otilde;ukogu 20. detsembri 1996. aasta otsuse 97/16/E&Uuml; (t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive- ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukomitee loomise kohta (6)) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 3 on s&auml;testatud, et komitee hoiab vajalikul m&auml;&auml;ral kontakti alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomiteega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS DECIDED AS FOLLOWS: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD J&Auml;RGMISE OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Standing Committee on Employment (hereinafter referred to as the 'Committee') shall be reformed in accordance with the provisions set out below. </inglise>
<eesti> Alalise t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivekomitee (edaspidi "komitee") &uuml;mberkorraldamine toimub koosk&otilde;las j&auml;rgmiste s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The task of the Committee shall be to ensure, in compliance with the Treaty and with due regard for the powers of the institutions and bodies of the Communities, that there is continuous dialogue, concertation and consultation between the Council, the Commission and the social partners in order to enable the social partners to contribute to the coordinated employment strategy and to facilitate coordination by the Member States of their policies in this field, taking into account the economic and social objectives of the Community as reflected in both the Employment Guidelines and the Broad Economic Policy Guidelines. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee &uuml;lesanne on tagada koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga ning &uuml;henduste institutsioonide ja organite volitusi n&otilde;uetekohaselt arvesse v&otilde;ttes pidev dialoog, koosk&otilde;lastamine ja konsulteerimine n&otilde;ukogu, komisjoni ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel, et t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled saaksid kaasa aidata koosk&otilde;lastatud t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivestrateegia edendamisele ja sellele, et liikmesriigid saaksid omavahel koosk&otilde;lastada selles valdkonnas tehtavat poliitikat, v&otilde;ttes arvesse nii t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivesuunistes kui ka majanduspoliitilistes &uuml;ldsuunistes esitatud &uuml;henduse majanduslikke ja sotsiaalseid eesm&auml;rke. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The members of the Council or their representatives, the Commission, and representatives of the social partners at European level shall take part in the work of the Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee t&ouml;&ouml;s osalevad n&otilde;ukogu liikmed v&otilde;i nende esindajad, komisjon ja Euroopa tasandi t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte esindajad. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> There shall be a maximum of 20 social partner representatives organised in two equal delegations, 10 from each side of industry. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooltel on maksimaalselt 20 esindajat jaotatuna kahte v&otilde;rdsesse delegatsiooni, m&otilde;lemal t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolel 10 esindajat. </eesti>
<inglise> The social partner's delegations shall cover the whole economy, being composed of European organisations representing either general interests or more specific interests of supervisory and professional staff and small and medium-sized businesses. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte delegatsioonid h&otilde;lmavad k&otilde;iki majandusvaldkondi ning koosnevad Euroopa organisatsioonidest, mis esindavad j&auml;relevalve- v&otilde;i erialat&ouml;&ouml;tajate ning v&auml;ikeste ja keskmise suurusega ettev&otilde;tete &uuml;ldisi huve v&otilde;i erihuve. </eesti>
<inglise> For this purpose, each delegation shall be made up of representatives of the organisations of social partners consulted by the Commission pursuant to the provisions of the Treaty concerning social policy and falling within the following categories: </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt asutamislepingu sotsiaalpoliitikat k&auml;sitlevatele s&auml;tetele konsulteerib komisjon igasse delegatsiooni kuuluvate esindajatega t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte organisatsioonidest, kes kuuluvad j&auml;rgmistesse kategooriatesse: </eesti>
<inglise> - general cross-industry organisations; </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjate vahelised &uuml;ldorganisatsioonid; </eesti>
<inglise> - cross-industry organisations representing certain categories of workers or undertakings, and </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjate vahelised organisatsioonid, kes esindavad teatavaid t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja ettev&otilde;tete kategooriaid, ja </eesti>
<inglise> - sectoral organisations representing agriculture and trade. </inglise>
<eesti> - valdkonnaorganisatsioonid, kes esindavad p&otilde;llumajandust ja kaubandust. </eesti>
<inglise> The practical coordination of the workers' delegation shall be undertaken by the European Trade Union Confederation (ETUC), and that of the employers' delegation by the Union of Industrial and Employers' Confederations of Europe (UNICE). </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;tajate delegatsiooni tegevuse praktiline koosk&otilde;lastaja on Euroopa Ameti&uuml;hingute Konf&ouml;deratsioon (ETUC) ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate delegatsiooni tegevuse koosk&otilde;lastaja on Euroopa T&ouml;&ouml;stuse ja T&ouml;&ouml;andjate Konf&ouml;deratsioonide Liit (UNICE). </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall notify the Chairman of the Committee on a regular basis of the list of the organisations referred to in paragraph 3. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab komitee eesistujale regulaarselt l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud organisatsioonide loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission will take account of possible changes in the way in which the two sides of industry are represented at European level. </inglise>
